Klecin [kltin] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Marcinowice, within widnica County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland.[1] Prior to 1945 it was in Germany. It lies approximately 12 kilometres (7mi) north-east of widnica, and 42 kilometres (26mi) south-west of the regional capital Wrocaw. The village has a population of 170. Coordinates: 505355N 163408E / 50.89861N 16.56889E / 50.89861; 16.56889
